parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intake Manifold Shutter Valve Screw Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold shutter valve screws can cause the screws to fall into the engine, leading to engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud rattling or knocking noise from the engine
engine stalling
loss of power
misfiring
and difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Side Seat Belt Latch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a potential safety risk in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt receiver falls apart
the male end will not connect to the female end
broken pieces are visible inside the buckle
the seat belt is stuck or difficult to latch
the seat belt warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the limited-slip differential can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when changing lanes at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle does not respond to acceleration
loss of power
especially when changing lanes at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts hard
the overdrive light flashes on and off
the check engine light stays on
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gearbox or linkage can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Leaking gear oil fluid at the linkage coupling
trouble going into reverse and sometimes into first gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can cause the seat belt to break, making it unable to hold the passenger, which can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt breaks into pieces
the seat belt will no longer hold the passenger.
